# --- COMMIT TEMPLATE ---
# type: Choose change type from below
#   feat:     New feature
#   fix:      Bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation only changes
#   style:    Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code
#   refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   test:     Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
#   chore:    Changes to build process or auxiliary tools and libraries
#   perf:     Performance improvement
#   ci:       Changes to CI configuration files and scripts
#   revert:   Revert previous commit
#
# subject: Summarize changes in 50 characters or less
#   - Use imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
#   - Start with lowercase letter
#   - No period at the end
#
# body: Focus on WHY detailed explanation (wrap at 72 characters)
#   - Explain the reason, background, and impact of the change
#   - Focus on "why" rather than "what"
#   - Use bullet points for multiple changes
#
# footer: Related Issue or Task numbers
#   - Closes #123
#   - Refs #456
#   - Task 6.1.2
#
# Example:
# feat: add bookmark functionality to exam questions
#
# Enable users to revisit important questions later by adding bookmark feature.
# Improve learning efficiency by providing review mechanism combined with incorrect questions.
#
# - Implement Bookmark model and API
# - Add frontend bookmark state management
# - Integrate bookmark button in existing question list screen
#
# Task 6.1.2